data.chText: 血压和呼吸也做了记录。
data.enText: Blood pressure and respiration are also recorded.

tr: the metabolic processes whereby certain organisms obtain energy from organic molecules
processes that take place in the cells and tissues during which energy is released and carbon dioxide is produced and absorbed by the blood to be transported to the lungs
the bodily process of inhalation and exhalation
the process of taking in oxygen from inhaled air and releasing carbon dioxide by exhalation
a single complete act of breathing in and out

example.ex: His respiration grew fainter throughout the day.
example.tran: 一天当中，他的呼吸越来越微弱。

partsOfSpeech.dec: a 加强 + spir 呼吸 + e → 看到渴望的东西就呼吸急促 → 热望
a 加强 + spir 呼吸 + ation，aspire 的名词 → 热望
con 共同 + spir 呼吸 + e → 同呼吸，共存亡 → 同谋
con 共同 + spir 呼吸 + acy 表状态，conspire的名词 → 共谋；反叛
dis 没有 + pirit〔= spirit 精神〕→ 使沮丧
ex 除去 + pir〔=spir〕呼吸 + e → 没有呼吸 → 断气，注意：ex后接s开头的词根缩写成ex
ex 除去 + pir〔=spir〕呼吸 + ation，expire 的名词 → 断气；期满
in 使… + spir 呼吸 + e → 使呼吸 → 吸气
in 使… + spir 呼吸 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 吸入灵气 → 找到灵感 → 灵感
per 贯穿 + spir 呼吸 + e → 全身呼吸 → 出汗
per 贯穿 + spir 呼吸 + ation，perspire 的名词 → 出汗
re 重复 + spir 呼吸 + e → 呼吸；恢复精神
spir 呼吸 + it → 深呼吸 → 精神
spirit 精神；情绪 + ual 有…性质的 → 精神上的；宗教的
tran〔s〕转移 + spir 呼吸 + e → 通过呼吸转移 → 泄露
